Chilean Stocks: La Polar Falls; E-CL and Soquimich Advance

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-31T21:05:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/chilean-stocks-empresas-la-polar-falls-soquimich-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:26 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.1 percent to 4,847.87, its fifth day
of gains.  E-CL SA (ECL CC) climbed for a second day, adding 1.5
percent to 1,373.9 pesos. The Chilean power generator is
scheduled to become a member of the MSCI  Chile  index tomorrow.
Chile’s government also authorized an increase in power rates in
northern Chile of between 0.3 percent and 0.9 percent, according
to an e-mailed statement.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 2.6 percent to
2,450.3 pesos. The Chilean department store chain declined for a
third straight day after announcing it plans to sell $400
million in new shares to fund expansion and shore up its
finances.  Soc. Quimica & Minera de Chile SA (SQM/B CC) gained 3.3
percent to 29,163 pesos, a record high. Chile’s largest
fertilizer producer rose after Citigroup Inc. increased its
ratings for peers The Mosaic Co. and Potash Corp of Saskatchewan
Inc. to “buy” from “hold.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  